# M2SQL Gateway - Installation & Setup Guide

This guide explains how to integrate the M2SQL Gateway into the Raymond Newman MUMPS (v1.71) engine. 

### Prerequisites
Before proceeding, ensure that you have SQLite installed on your system. If not, install it using your package manager:
```bash
sudo apt-get install sqlite3 libsqlite3-dev


Step 1: Download Raymond Newman MUMPS Core
​Do not clone the entire Newman system into this repository. Instead, follow these steps:
​Download the official Raymond Newman MUMPS v1.71 source code from SourceForge.
​Extract the downloaded archive onto your local environment.
​Stop right before running the compilation (make) process.
​Step 2: Inject M2SQL Runtime Files
​Locate the runtime/ directory generated within your extracted Newman MUMPS folder.
​Copy the 4 files located under the runtime/ folder of this Git repository and paste them directly into that local runtime/ directory, overwriting any existing files if prompted.
​Step 3: Replace the Makefile
​Go to the installation/ directory in this Git repository and locate the customized Makefile.
​Replace the original Makefile in the root of your local Newman MUMPS folder with this customized version.
​Compile the system by running:
Step 4: Import MUMPS Routines
​Once the system compiles and starts successfully through its standard path, import the global M2SQL utilities into your UCIs:
​Perform a ROUTINE RESTORE (using ^%RR) for the % routines into the MGR UCI to ensure global system-wide availability.
​Perform a ROUTINE RESTORE for the application routines into your standard workspace UCI, or alternatively into your test environment (e.g., TST UCI).
